Oh ya I forgot one more thing







Hockey is back 

Wahoooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooo
oooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooooo
ooooooooooooooooooooooooooo!

Sunday: After church I hung out with Jay for a little while.  We watched Sandlot 2.  That movie was one of the funniest movies I have ever seen.  This is simply because it was one of the worst movies I've ever seen. I love movies like that.  They are so terrible they are good.  

Monday night I played hockey with Pinto and the gang again.  It was one hell of a work out.  I gave some of my older equipment to Ricky's little brother Bobby.  I felt good because so many people have helped me with equipment so I got a chance to give back.  Also it's difficult because not many people are smaller than me.  Bobby is.

Wednesday night I spoke at church for the Senior Graduation ceremony.  I was very fluent and sounded like a grown up according to my mother and Jess.  I was also funny and added in the use of Giggidy Giggidy. My right leg was shaking the entire time I was up there but I was able to stay calm in my speech.  It was so weird looking at all the younger kids because I felt like I was in their place just yesterday.  Time really flies.  After that I played hockey at Iceworks with John Weinderman and Alan Hahn.  John is the Islanders radio announcer for those of you who don't know.  Alan is the writer for the New York Islanders in Newsday.    We had a goalie named Ernie who is a real gamer.  He is a 50 year old Canadian who just moved to LI in September.  While in the locker room we had some great hockey talk.  It's cool because I am such a young kid and they are veterans who really know the game.  However, I am able to talk with them because I know my hockey.  They gave me some insight on the old school hockey.  It was only four of us plus Ernie on the rink.  We got the ice for free because we know the guy who cuts the ice.  John was showing me some stretches and giving me pointers on break out plays and rushes up the ice.  He also called me a natural born fore checker.    He has really taken a liking to me which makes me feel so cool.  A guy who knows the game of hockey thinks I am a talented young player.  Anyways I got to put on the goalie gloves and play a little goalie at the end.  I had my regular equipment on with the goalie blocker and catching glove.  I made some diving glove saves which feels so cool.  Afterwards we talked again about the conspiracy over this year Stanley Cup Finals and how the Flames should have won the cup.  Afterwards I was talking to John and Joe( the zamboni man) about Women's hockey.  We discussed the conspiracy of the Women's Olympic Team in 1998 because John's wife was on it but got kicked off.  Stupid Cammy Granato.  

Last night Jess and I saw Batman Begins.  Besides a few cheesy parts the movie was excellent.  I thought the photography was sick and the story was dark and mysterious.  Afterwards we went to Walbaums and bought  stuff to makes smores.  We were inspired by the Sandlot.  We went back to her house and made smores over candles in her room.  It was very original.  We used tweezers to hold the chocolate over the candles.   We had a lot of fun yesterday.  She drove me home and we talked in her car till like 4 in the morning.  I am glad I can be there for Jess.  I want to brighten up her days as much as I can.  Thank you for all the fun we have had all summer so far.


I HAVE TO MOVE.  This sucks big time.  Will my mom ever catch a break.  I really hate all the garbage she has had to go through.  I wish she just wouldn't be so stressed and upset all the time.  Feel better mom.

So the last few days have been pretty filled up.  I brought Jess to church with me on Sunday, which I hope made some sort of internal impact, even if not spoken aloud.  The message was all about faith to endure which is something both me and my mom know a lot about.  I wish my mom was there honestly.  She would love the new pastor as do I.  After church on Sunday I went to an arena football game with Jay and some of my old friends from Island Trees.  Then me and Jay hungout at his house after and played some wiffleball.  I know I am a loser but wiffleball friggin rules.  Sorry it is the third best sport next to ultimate frisbee and hockey.  After that me and Jess hungout for a little but she was getting seepy so she just went home.  

Monday me and Jess went to the beach near her house and we had a catch.  I think it's so cool that Jess is good at sports yet not a tom boy.  She is girly in the girly areas yet can actually engage in physical activites.  She can play them well also.  Our game ended when I crushed the ball into the ocean.  Then we decided to have a little family/friend that you like dinner at me house.  I was feeling upset because other people were talking about doing family oriented things.  So me and Jess went food shopping and bought stuff to cook dinner.  She also took a picture of me wearing a lucky charms hat which looked god awful but it was hilarious.  She sure knows her produce.  She described peas as putrid which is just awesome.  We cooked dinner for my mom which my mom thought was a pleasant surprise.  It was fun although I am not that great of a cook.  Jess and I also did dishes and helped clean everything up.  After that me and Jess when to go hangout with my friends Erica and Jon.  We watched Anchorman which is just insanely ridiculous.  Clearly   Brick is the best character although Ron runs a close second.

Today I started my first day back at Herr's Super Deli.  I love and hate that place all at once.  The customers are still dumb, the food is still overpriced, the owner is still non-existant, the employees are still saracastic.  I love it.  I hate it.  Honestly, the man who added the word super between the word Herr's and Deli subconsciously knew that this deli was going to be a madhouse.  You could be tripping on acid and still wouldn't be able to script stuff that goes on inside the confines of those century old walls and floors.  It was like riding a bike.  I haven't lost it.  I was a different clerk too.  It was nice being back.  I am only working 25 hours this week but it should build up as the days pass.  When I got home I made a makeshift workout bench and decided to start working out again while at home.

Something inside me doesn't feel right though.  I truly  feel melancholy.  One moment I am happy the next  I am feeling uneasy about life.  It's kinda scary.  I also really feel bad for my mom and what happened to her.  Please pray for her for those of you who read this and choose to do so.  So here are lyrics to the song Pull the String off Mudvayne's new album Lost and Found.  I feel lost yet I seem to always find myself  right after that.  The only problem is that I get lost again.  I hate the game of hide and seek.

So Wednesday after Meghan left I chilled out for a while.  I went to dinner with Chuck.  Then after that Rachael came over to study Geology.  I was like wow two beautiful girls in my room on the same day go Charlie.  It just sucked that the first time me and Rachael hung out outside of class was to study for Geology.  We had a blast though.  I spilled protein on her by accident but right away cleaned it off her.  She had the services of me whiping her sticky feet.  I am such a nice boy.  We got off task a lot talking about anything and everything.  We seemed to flirt a little bit.  Like when I gave her some peanuts and said, "Would you like to have some of my nuts."  I was making her laugh hysterically.  I was even like, "Your so damn cute."  Because she says she is a loser but she is not.  She is random like me and it was soooooo much fun.  Too bad we didn't get to hangout outside of class.  I told her we would have had a blast.  I walked her back to her room to protect her from anyone who might hurt her like a gentleman would do.  We talked about the Simpsons and I made her laugh.  She really is so cool even though she doesn't think so.  On the way back I listened to Mudvayne partially because I felt so good about that day and partially because I am a scaredy cat.  I was singing and getting really into it.  I got back to my room and studied for a while.  T.J. came back to my room and apologized about not understanding my ADHD as well as he thought he did.  It felt good because I thought he thought I was annoying.  I also think it felt good because I  respected him as an RA.  I tried to go to bed around four but couldn't sleep.  I wound up staying up all night.  I got into the final on no sleep.  I memorized the questions from previous tests and got done with the first 60 in like 20 mins.  The second half was ehhh but I think I did well.  I think I migh have pulled a 3.8 this semester.  

Right after the final I packed up my stuff and checked out.  Then we helped John move his stuff out.  T.J. had tried to be a sneaky snake and put a waterballoon on my doorknob so it would break when I woke up.  It didn't work so to get him back I had an elaborate plan.   taped a ballon to the top of his window on the outside of his room.  This way when he closed it it would get crushed in the window and go all over him.  I don't know if it worked but it still was a good plan.  We then went to eat at the campus center.  Bereza said some funny comments about thinking that a man was a woman.  We went back to Bombard's and watched a movie and then went to bed.

The next day we woke up and had lunch with Meghan.  She was really cool to get to know and she seemed to like me and think I was funny.  I walked her over to get something done and then we layed on the grass at Collin's for a little.  I wiped the grass off her booty and then we went to Erics room.  I took a nap and they went to visit  Jesse.  I woke up and watched XMen while waiting for them to come back.  When they did we went to Friendly's. The waitress was cool and I made her laugh a lot.  There were some girls their who seemed to be checking me out and being flirty but it was weird.  I got a spit ball shot at me and didn't know how to read that.  They were tall but were probably still in high school.  The one girl stuck her bootaay out while I was walking by.  We then went to Bombard's and jammed for a while.  We played One by U2.  It felt so cool playing drums to a song.  I also rocked the bass in my muscle shirt. We then went to bed.  

We woke up today and went to say goodbye to Eric.  We then helped Bower move more of his stuff.  We then went to Bereza's graduation.  It was nice.  Then for moving his stuff out Bower and his parents took us out to dinner.  It was nice place and I had fun.  After that we went back to Bombards and chilled outside in front of a fire with his parents and brother.  We then jammed for a little and then I showed him some music.  Bombard cut my hair and then I worked out and showered.  It feels cool to like live with a family.  I would have loved to have an older brother

My sister his home and is going to go to a Christian rehab so finally things will become different.  I have also been talking to mymom and it seems God is answering prayer.  Tomorrow's entry will focus on the year in review.

So the last few days have gone by pretty smooth in most areas.  I just took my Communication Theory final and found out that I got a 91.5.  Only 14 other kids got over a 90 and it's a big class so I get proud.  I also took my English final yesterday and it was pretty easy.  I got my paper back from that class and got an 18-20.  I found out I can write college papers, which is good, because I'll be getting a lot of them.  I have still been consistently working out.  I worked out yesterday by myself.  I was the smallest and shortest guy down there but that's ok.  Guys were cheering me on while doing bench press.  When I was trying to put up 145, and kind of struggling, the guy was like, "C'mon push it."  I was like ahhhhhhh and put it up 2 more times.     That brought me to a total of putting it up 4 times which may not seem like a lot but I only flipping weigh 135.  I feel so cool lifting a lot of weight.... I'm not gonna lie.  This is especially because I am such a little boy.  Last night things got smooothiied up with Susieeeeee and I hope it stays that way.  The situation still sucks for me but I wanna at least be friendly.  This is just for this point in time.  We will see what happens in the future.  Thanks for calling.  

Today I woke up and did laundry with Tom.  My muscle shirts shrunk and they look good on me.  I still feel weird wearing them though.  But ehhh I'll get used to it.  I then ate lunch with Meghan and Tom on Indian.  I ate like a beast eats.  Tom had to leave to study so after that it was just Meghan and I.  We had a good talk and it seems she doesn't just look at me like some 18 year old hyper boy anymore.  I really don't want people to look at me like that, but I guess I contribute to it.  Then I brought her back to my room and showed her some Mudvayne.  She got interested which is cool because she's from the country LOL.  She was really tired so I am letting her sleep on my bed right now as we write and read.  I have worship music on and am trying to accommodate her as best as me can.  No don't worry it's not like that.  I am just a nice boy.  Guys are all like you have a girl alone in your room go for it.  I am like, "Hi let me introduce myself.  My name is Charlie and I have morals."  Plus I already like someone and wouldn't do that.  It's so funny how people automatically assume all guys want some.  Jeez.  It only further propagates the stereotype that guys are asses.  I am not one of those guys.

I have one final left and then I am done.  Honestly, for the most part I hated Albany.  But this last semester I have grown close to a lot of people.  Tom, Chuck and I are the upstanding citizens of Seneca.  Johnny and I are all hardcore.  I have worked out with several people and that's cool.  I loved Impact and the people I met.  Everyone said that I am crazy, funny and hyper.  I will be missed and will miss them.      Rachael became like my best friend all semester.  I did well in my classes.  And most of all I am still straightedge.  The NUMBER 1 PARTY SCHOOL GOT OWNED UUUBERLY!  Now it's almost time to go home and face the music with certain things.  I also have a lot of opportunities though.  It should be an interesting summer.  Well that's it for now.

So the last few days have gone by very smoothly.  Jess and I had another good conversation last night about a lot of different things.  Wednesday was spent mostly studying for Business Law and downloading music and movies.  I now have 2300 songs and 39 movies on my computer.  I couldnt get to sleep Wednesday until 6 in the morning which kinda sucked.  But I woke up at like 1 and studied some more.  I took my final and pretty much owned it vertically, and horizontally.  I think I got an A in that course which is cool.  My teacher was awesome and we learned a lot.  For example did you know that someone could sue you if they get injured while trespassing on your property.  Thats insane.  On the final he put a question that was written like this:
a)yay the course if over no more studying (note this is the correct answer)
b)continue to study over the summer for business law (note this is the incorrect answer)

After the final I worked out with Johnny and bench pressed 145 again which is a big confidence booster.  I always used to suck at bench press and I feel cool now that I can do a lot.  I am such a loser when it comes to being all like yay about bench press.  It's the hardcore strong Charlie and the baby coming out all at once.  

Susie hasn't really been on my mind so thats good.  I'm definitely getting over what she did and that's good.  It lingers, but isn't bothering me as much as it is a shocker.  I think this is mostly because of Jess, my friends, and a jam packed summer ahead of me.  My life has really transformed since becoming a Christian and it really hasn't fully sunk in yet.  I think it's because its still transforming which is so cool to witness.  Anyways today I am going to play frisbee because I love it oh so much.  3 Finals left and then Ohio baby.  It is going to be insane.  


Random Thoughts From the other day:  How is it not clear?  I am just not interested right now.  That is not mean especially when talking about a livejournal that I can't even read.  Words are more important than pictures to me.  What do you want from me right now? I want to be your friend.  But then I think about it and wonder if there is any good reason for me to be your friend at least at this point in time.  You are being friendly to me at this point which is nice I guess, but does it make up for what you did?  At this point probably not.  It's harsh but true.  I still love you and care about you but man is it hard to not get upset or angry.  God will help me do that part.  Don't assume anything.  Don't think I'll find a family like yours.  They are rare although your used to it because you lived with them your whole life.
These words were spoken softly in my mind not in an angry way.     

Whered you go? Did you run away?  Are you lost?  Can you be found?  Only you can find yourself nobody else.  When you do find yourself, do you dare stare the truth in the mirror.  I miss the old you.  Do you miss the old you? Please don't be hurt by my words that this situation has caused me to feel.  Remember Charlie don't try to teach lessons that one can only learn on their own.

Yesterday was me and Rachael's final embarkment on the terrible journey that was Comm Theory.  We only had class for a little so it wasn't that bad.  We got our papers back.  I got a 94 which I am very pleased about.  On my first English paper I didn't do so swell.  So it was nice to know that I can write a college paper and do ok on it. Afterwards we talked like we usually do about life.  It was nice to have someone this year who understood what I was talking about.  I know now I am not crazy.

So last night was the Impact Bonfire.  It was ridonkulous.  This is the new word  me and Tom came up with.  So if you don't like the spelling.... well.... then it doesn't matter because its as friggin made up word.  I went with Chuck to drive to Ted's.  We listened to Christian hardcore and talked about ADHD and stuff.  He has it too so we had a good discussion.  We got there around 8.  It was a bit nippy.  It's friggin May and its still cold.  Damn that wind conducive Albany.  It was fun for the most part.  The bonfire was huge.  Me and Fitz took some funny pictures where we looked like Beasts.  Cuddly beasts though.  After I got back I talked on the phone with Jess for a while.  We talked about how we should play hockey and soccer together.  I brought up how I used to be a soccer goalie but then the nets got  bigger and I didn't so that was the end of that LOL.  I was acting sorta cheesey but assured her it was no lie.  I don't lie with my cheese I stand up LOL.  She thinks I am a dork which is not to be confused with a nerd.  Dorks are cool nerds are just dumb, ironically. 

Recently Simpsons episodes and Family Guy episodes have been relating to my life which is strangely fitting.  Anyway heres some interesting stuff.   I grew some chest hair that was not there about 3.56 days ago.  Has to be the weightlifting.  Also, I think Brand New has the obligation to change their name to Sorta Old and then maybe We've Been Our For a While after a certain time period.  There was also a carpet in our suite bathroom this morning.  I have no idea where it came from.  But that's just awesome.  I mean now my delicate feet will be cushioned by the soft fabrics of what ever the hell carpets are made of.  Awesome.  Anyways I gotta go study for Business Law.  

I am going to be speaking at my church when I go home which is sweet.  I can't wait and I hope people go to the Senior Night to hear me speak.

After church yesterday the ride back to campus was quite insane. Justine almost killed us several times. I repeatedly said, "All day" to Emanuel. It took us like thirty years to find Price Chopper to drop off Emanuel. When I arrived back on campus, I ate lunch with Scott, Tom, Chuck and Stella. Our lunch talk was very interesting. I was very hyper and made very funny comments on an array of non-related topics. After lunch I played some frisbee with Scott, Stella, Tom, and T.J. There was some untimely wind which caused some pretty catastrophic frisbee-like events. After frisbee I was chillen in my room and received a survey about study habits. Dennis and I joked about how it would be all zeros for him, and I should put some crazy number that wasn't even possible.  I am very modestly cocky about my grades and study habits.  I'm such a nerd. But not really.  We also talked about the Psych supplement for Savare.  OMG that man is ridiculous.  Thank God I didn't have him first semester.  He makes you by this workbook just so he can obtain more money.  It's basically his textbook with everything blank.  You have to fill it out for him.  It is the most insane peice of work ever in life.  We also joked about how our garbage bag is like a body bag and could be used to hide humans. Muhahhaa. Or you know we could just throw a loooooot of garbage in there. It reminded me how I have been obsessively clean all year which is a shocker for me.  Our bathroom isn't on the other hand.  It is a private bathroom and gets used more than the girls from the third floor.  It is more open than 7 Eleven.  In random news, somebody I know saw Dane Cook.  I was like psahah whoa.  We then started imitating all of his skits.  So anyway, later that night I had to start my paper.  This came after I watched the new Family Guy.  It was hilarious besides the fact that it ripped on The Passion.  After the episode, I worked on my paper in Tom's room because my computer is an evil, evil machine that I have to have utter dependence on.  It took we a while just to write the intro but after that the words came to me.  In the middle of writing the paper I got a phone call from Susie.  It was very unexpected and we talked about some things.  I cleared up most of my emotions.  I was very pleased with how I spoke to her.  I got out what I needed to say in a firm but respectful manner.  I was actually asking God to present a situation so I can restate my words.  I had previously talked to Susie's parents and Aunt about it and I felt like an adult.  I like how I can talk with older people and still understand a lot of what they are saying.  Especially when it comes to life situations.  Anyhow,  I still have some things I would like to say but I will wait until the situation cools down.  After that I finished my paper by like 2:30 in Tom's room.  I was quite happy with the way it came out.  I couldn't fall asleep though.  I couldn't stop thinking about certain things.  At 4 in the morning, I got the sudden urge to listen to music.  I put on my Ipod and took about my drumsticks.  I just started drumming on my wall, legs, and fan while listening to it.  I was getting so into it.  I really want to be a drummer for something.  I will try to be next year at Messiah.  I fell asleep around like 7 and woke up at 10.  I fell asleep with my drumsticks.

I edited my paper real quick and went to Geology.  Rachael didn't go which made it super boring.  We had to fill out evaluations.  I joked with some kid about how we should fill in the female bubble instead of the male.  Nobody wouldn't notice because it is anonymous.  We would screw up the whole system.  And no one would ever know.  Except of course for those of you who read this.  After the class I talked to my teacher about evolution.  I told him I didn't believe in it.  He's a flippin geology teacher.  And I told him I don't believe in evolution and the Big Bang Theory.  He must have peed his pants.  After that I had my final English class.  I loved it.  We handed in our crap and filled out evaluations.  Afterwards I went up to my English teacher and told her how I loved the class and how I might minor in English.  I joked about how I hated reading coming into college and this class caused a shift in my mindset.

After that Bombard, Scott, and I worked out.  I benched 145 lbs. That is more than I weigh.  I was so surprised with myself.  I also lifted 55 lb dumbells on another excercise.  I love that number.  Right after that we went to First Monday at Grace Church.  I have loved Manday Monday all year and this was the final one.    We got to eat dinner there like usual.  I had 3 plates of food.  Ridiculous.  We then went into worship.  I was drumming on the chairs and singing at the same time.  I loved all the songs they played.  They were, Blessed Be The Name,  Here I am To Worship, and  Open the Eyes of My Heart.  We had to leave early to go to Mikey's concert.

We got there at 8 exactly.  I drove with Chris.  We talked about things in my life which was cool.    We listened to Norma Jean.  They are Christian hardcore, which I never knew. At the concert, I got to see the Percussion Ensemble perform.  It was awesome.  I was actually able to play along with an African song they played simply by looking at the kid drumming.  I can't read drum music too well but I can play stuff by watching and listening.  It reminded my of my band days and how I really want to become a drummer in something.  I have been thinking about that a lot recently.  We chilled outside the concert hall a little bit afterwards.  Fitz and I were doing some wrestling stuff like little boys.  I then came back to Indian and that's been it recently.  Tomorrow is my last Comm Theory class with Rachael.  We had some fun times in class.  I will miss it.  Then starts finals.  The first one I will own is Business Law on Thursday.  I hope you feel better Jess.  I will make you laugh and keep you company.

So today I woke up at like 9:45 but didn't get out of bed until like 10:12.  I got all snazzzzzzzy for church.  I wore a shirt and tie which was something I haven't done in a while.  Besides the little gash of hairlessness in my head I looked pretty good LOL.  I went outside and thought my ride had left which would have sucked.  It is going to be one of the last times I see George in a while so I wanted to go to Loudonville.  My ride wound up coming which was cool.  The sermon was great.  I took notes like a little nerd.  Yes I know I am a loser.  The pastor talked about vital relationships within the church and how Christians should have relationships with others outside the church.  He brought up a good point.  He said, "How can you a relationship with God (invisible)  if you can't have one with human followers (flesh). He talked about how too much bible teaching can create pride and arrogance but you still need it as a foundation.  And how relationships are key.  It applied to my life right now.  I am on fire for God but get too proud.  I don't like that.  I confessed my sins of the last month.  I apologized for what I have done to others as well as myself.  I need to change Charlie for Charlie and nobody else.  Sometimes I feel like I learn lessons a second too late.  Then I can't change the past and it kills me.  So then I want to take action to change the previous wrong action.  And sometimes action is the worst thing to do in some situations.  I need to step back.  Cool down.  After the service I spoke to the speaker and the Pastor of the church.  He asked me if I felt called to ministry.  I was like uuhuhfwhats.  Maybe I will be a youth minister.  How cool would that be.  I will act just like the kids when I am like 37 because of my ADHD.  He gave me a book called Basic Christianity.  It was cool. The first page talked about how young adults dislike institutionalism in the church but love the big J.C.  He is a really nice guy.  I told him a little about my background and how it was similar to George's.  That's it for now.  I'll probably be writing again soon.  For all 2 of you who are interested.

So here is an entry on just my general thoughts.  Lately I have been thinking about life and who I am and maturity and what others are like.  I have come to this conclusion that consistency is difficult to find in the words and actions of most kids my age.  Saying one thing one day and than another thing the next is not consitency even if you believe one thing strongly one day and something different the next.  Values are also different from actions and meaningless unless applied in real life situations.  I have also learned that I try too hard and am too apologetic.  Sometimes stepping back and taking no action is the best action.  The further you push someone the more they will pull away.  So for this I am sorry for pushing.  I am sorry for the drama even though I am not my mom.  This doesn't give someone the right to curse at her.  However, you created this situation.  And it is not mostly my fault.  It takes two to not get along.  I also don't like the words, "I guess so."  It implies stubborness.  I don't think you did anything on purpose but do think someone things should have obviously not been done.  Confidence in the heart is a lot more important than confidence through words.  Changing isn't neccesarily maturing.  I also gotta not try to teach people lessons that they don't want to deal with or can't deal with.  Some lessons are learned on your own.  Not dealing with things is the simple way out but builds no character.  I can't believe how things have changed from caring to not wanting to talk to unless I am dying.  That is not care.  I still care for you and would do more than just pray.  I don't mean to sound like a preacher but someone people need to hear certain things if they don't come to conclusions on their own.  Squidgily was our term.  You shouldn't be supporting someone who wants to kick someone's ass when it is not their fault.  You can't control someone elses actions and their actions should not be seen as mine.  There is a such thing as a half truth.  Maybe  you have been harsh to push me away.  But it is still not right.  I am not an object to either be dealt with or not.  I am a human and expect to be treated like one.  Regardless of how you view me.  I want the drama to end as well.  I hate drama.  But I also don't like mean people.  I had a good talk to today with Jeane.  She is really smart and we talked about a lot of things.  My Ipod and computer are also working which made me happy.   Anyway that is all for now.  Is caring the same as love?

So the last couple of days have been interesting.  Classes went fine although they were boring.  Jess and I have been having a lot of fun talking on the phone.  She is a really smart person when it comes to life situations.  I can tell her some interesting things and she will understand where I am coming from.  I can't wait to come home in the summer and hangout with her.  Yesterday I watched the Ghostbusters with T.J. Tom and Chuck.  That is a great movie.  Dan Akroid is uberly funny.  Everybody else in Seneca was extremely drunk.  So Tom, Chuck and I decided that we are going to make a facebook group called the Biggest Drunks in Seneca.  I love the irony.  Chuck has drank two beers and a shot.  Tom and I have both never drank.  So theres some good news when I come home in the summer.  I might be a youth leader at my home church.  This is awesome because I would have never thought that they would have chose me.  I was the one who was the most skeptical dude there was.  But God transforms people and it's awesome to see.  My mom has done some things in the last two days that have bothered not only me but others.  However, I have talked to a group of parents who still love me and care for me.  Thanks for the advice and the reassurance.  It also seems like those other people are going to get bothered at me even though they said they wouldn't.  I've been cursed and threatened to have my ass kicked by someone who doesn't even know the full situation.  But that's ok because I'll just go hockey style LOL.  J/K I am not a fighter.  I am a hockey player.  (Irony).  A particular person has also said that they don't want to talk to me unless I am dying.  This same person said they care about me.  Hows that for caring.  I am also becoming a preacher which is apparently a bad thing.  Although we as Christians go to church every Sunday to hear someone preach.  I am no pastor by any means but do like to help others.  I will apologize for anything I have done in the last month and just let the situation cool.  I am still hurt by some things that occurred but I can't change things no matter how hard I try.  Sometimes me trying to hard is a bad thing.  You just have to keep things simple sometimes.  My conclusion to this situation so far is that 18 year olds are immature.  No matter how mature we think we are we are not.  I am 18 thus I am immature as well.  I do believe however that when humans experience things in life like pain it builds character an maturity.  This is only when that person takes that pain and allows God to make a transformation in that human.  I have also learned that God knows what's in your heart even when you don't or when you think you know better.  He has taught me a lot and I hope it can help me in the future.  The timing of all these events that occurred really sucked.  I was so ready to be Charlie again.  But my mom messed that up and so did a certain situation.  But you know what I still am Charlie even if certain people don't see it.  Some things are meant to be learned but never are.  I can't be the one to teach everybody so I will stop that right now.  Some of the greatest lessons learned are the ones on your own and through dealing with a rough situation.  

I just want to say thanks to the people who have helped me through this time.  You gals are very admirable.  I can't wait to come home and kiss you.  You know who you are.  I am going to squidgel you all over and we are going to rub noses together.

So on Tuesday was the Mudvayne concert.  The concert was ridiculous.  I took the trip with my friend John and his two friends Matt and Pat.  I met Susie at the venue.  The other bands that played were alright but when Mudvayne came on I regained my once lost energy especially in my legs.  I crowd surfed like 4 times, one of which I was screaming the lyrics to Silenced right in front of Chad's face.  In the moshpit I was jumping around like a mad man.  I got rocked in the head, neck, and ribs but I am fine.  There were actually times where I'd be the only person in the middle and people on the outside would just watch me and cheer me on.  I felt so crazy.  Susie saw me mosh a little and was probably scared.  We sung some songs together and although she hasn't listened to Mudvayne in a while and didn't have fun at first, she had fun once Mudvayne came on.  She said they definitely put on a good show and she likes Chad a lot.  He is really awesome.  Not only does he and the rest of the band have great stage presence but he has a heart.  In the intro to World So Cold he talked about the bravery of the soldiers overseas and the unity of New York that was evident during September 11th.  Susie and me flirted a little bit and I kept her safe as I promised.  I had a lot of fun with her and I hope she had fun too.  She said though that she looked at me and had no feelings for me but that's ok it was only a Mudvayne concert.

After the show when Susie was picked up the three of us went over to Virgin Megastores to meet them.  They were awesome.  Ryan thought I was crazy for telling him he is the best bassist in rock.  My friend talked to him next and when Ryan was like, "This kid is crazy," my friend was like, "You don't understand how much this kid loves you."  Ryan smiled.  I told Matt that I was a drummer and that he is amazing.  He had the funniest most modestly cocky reaction of, "You don't need to tell me that I know."  I told Chad about how his lyrics were inspirational and how I know what real bad parenting is about.  He gave me like a half hug and a pat on the back and said a heartfelt thank you.  After the show we made a crucial stop to White Castle where we had to wait like 30 years because the people in front of us ordered like 40 burgers.  After that we slept at the kid Matt's house.  Johnny told me that for a kid who has never drank or done drugs I am pretty flippin nuts.  It was a compliment.  

The next day we came back up very early in the morning.  We got a speeding ticket on the way home which was kind of interesting.  That night at Impact clips of Miracle were shown and I related to them to Christianity bein a family.  Then after that I spoke about what I learned this semester and my life story.  I was so cool calm and collective and people said I did really well.  I felt proud.  That is the first time I have spoke like that in public and didn't have stage fright.

Today Communication Theory was very fun simply because of Rachael.  We have sooo much fun writing our notes back and forth to each other during class.  It is so child like but it's cute.  I make her laugh a lot and it makes me feel confident.  I also told her I had a teeny crush on her and she said that was cute.  She really is just such a cool person to be around.  I was about this morning till about like 4 writing my paper which came out really good.  Thank God it's over.  Now I can breather until finals.  I then got a package from my mom after class containing my Mudvayne cd poster and t-shirt.  It also contained cotton socks and pens which are crucial to my life right now.

Me and Susie decided to start with a clean slate with each other.  She finally admitted to how she has been acting recently and it was a relief.  It was painful for her but pain is the best way to learn from mistakes and change yourself.  It's not the easy way out but it's the healthiest.  We still have some things to work out but I think it was a good step for us.  I was glad I could comfort her and I will help her on her way to changing for the better.  If theres anyone who knows about change its me.  That's all for now.
